Produces code for sorting the array primary, which also permutes the additional arrays given in the same way. Source   Edit   
macro foldArgsR(op: untyped; initial: untyped; args: varargs[untyped]): untyped

Folds over a variable number of arguments, potentially with different types.

This particular fold is right associative, meaning it starts at the end and the first argument gets evaluated last:

foldArgsR(x, f, [1,2,3]) is equivalent to f(1, f(1, f(2, f(3, x)))).
